HTML
WHAT IS HTML - HyperText Markup Language
WHY HTML IS USED - structures web content
What is Emmet & List 5 Emmet - Emmet --> Shortcut (e.g: ! → Boilerplate, ul>li*5 → Creates a list with 5 items, div.container → <div class="container"></div>, 
a[href="https://example.com"] → Creates a link,p{Hello World} → <p>Hello World</p>)
SHORT CUT CREATE of Emmet Boiler plate of HTML - !/html:5
WHAT STRUCTURE OF HTML
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <!-- Head Section -->
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Body Section -->
</body>
</html>
WHAT IS **HEAD** TAG - contains metadata, title, links to CSS, and scripts.
WHAT IS BODY  - contains the visible content of the web page.
IMPORTANT 3 ELEMENTS OR TAGS - <html>, <head>, <body>
WHAT IS DIFFERENT B/W ELEMENTS & TAGS IN HTML
Tag: The actual markup (<p>, <h1>, <a>)
Element: The tag with content (<p>Hello</p>)
CSS
WHAT IS CSS - Cascading Style Sheets
WHY IS CSS - used to style HTML elements
HOW TO CONNECT HTML & CSS , Tell the emmet Shortcut - link:css
HOW TO GET FONT & COLOR , IMAGE, CDN
  Fonts: Google Fonts (fonts.google.com)
  Colors: CSS or color palette tools
  Images:<img> tag
  CDN: Use Bootstrap, Tailwind, or other CDN links
BASIC CSS FAMILY : Text Family, Color & Background Family, Box Model
  Text Family: font-size, font-weight, line-height
  Color & Background Family: color, background-color, background-image
  Box Model: margin, padding, border, width, height
WHEN TO USE **BACKGROUND IMG** VS **IMG TAG**
  background-image → Use when you need to place text over an image.  
  <img> tag → Use when the image itself is the content, as text cannot be placed inside it.
WHAT IS LAYOUT & Explain About flexbox Properties
Layout defines page structure using utility classes (Flexbox, Grid).  
Flexbox Properties 
  - flex → Enables Flexbox  
  - flex-row / flex-col → Sets direction  
  - justify-center → Aligns items horizontally  
  - items-center → Aligns items vertically  
  - flex-wrap → Controls wrapping
WHAT IS TAILWIND CSS & WHY IS IT USED - Tailwind CSS is a utility-first CSS framework used for fast and responsive styling.
